  {
    "title": "It\u2019s quite embarrassing to see such irresponsible reporting from UNB, a respecte...",
    "description": "It\u2019s quite embarrassing to see such irresponsible reporting from UNB, a respected news agency in the country. Both the Emirates News Agency (WAM), the official news agency of the UAE, and BSS of Bangladesh clearly stated that Bangladesh's Prime Minister called the President of the United Arab Emirates to discuss the implications of the ongoing military escalation between Israel, the US, and Iran, with a focus on regional security and stability. But then you look at UNB's headline \u2014 it tells a completely different story. Who are they trying to mislead or should I say embarrass? Since UNB is a major news agency, several other outlets picked up the same incorrect headline: 'UAE President calls PM Tarique, discusses urgency to halt Middle East military escalation,' when it should clearly have been the other way around. Very irresponsible, UNB.",
    "link": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid0recf6Pipb9LXptjjLCAiKQJLZ7Gr6oae7PfoW328eNpoubNB98tVDLhh7GqzB7xPl",
